    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The biggest nightmare at King's Cross during transfers is usually the bottlenecking around platform changes, like a massive rush of tired commuters all trying to move toward the main exit, a phenomenon I call the \"Plat-Dash.\" Sometimes, you might just get lost in the sheer scale of the station, wandering toward the wrong exit, which is easily fixed with a quick glance at real-time signage. It's a bit like a large, slightly disorganized party where everyone is moving for a different reason.\n\nInterestingly, if you move through the station with purpose, you can minimize this stress. I’d recommend using the station map app beforehand to visualize your route from the Heathrow Express arrival area to the LNER boarding zone. This preparation will save you from getting caught up in the frantic energy of the crowds. Don't let the station overwhelm you; think of it as a choreographed, slightly chaotic dance between trains.",
      "source": "target",
